cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.IT, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new extension of the lambda calculus and studies its properties, including confluence and normalization. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with a functional programming language and its properties. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the distributivity isomorphism of simple types and its impact on the calculus. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper introduces a new computational interpretation of a mathematical concept (distributivity isomorphism) and studies its properties. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also less likely but still possible as the paper deals with a formal language (the lambda calculus) and its extension.
